STG top > Optimal schedules for prototype STG

Optimal Schedule Length for STG Version 2.0

This page represents optimal schedule lengths of Standard Task Graph Set Version 2.0. These optimal schedules were found by a practical parallel optimization algorithm PDF/IHS (Parallelized Depth First/Implicit heuristic Search) on a shared main memory multiprocessor system Sun Ultra80 Model 4450 (ultra80). Ultra80 has 4 Ultra SPARC IIs 450MHz CPUs and 1GB shared main memory. The upper limit on the search time was set to 10 minutes because of NP-completeness of the scheduling problem. In tables bellow, for some scheduling problems which PDF/IHS using 4 processors could not find an optimal schedule, the optimal schedule length are shown like "157-165"; it means that the upper bound for the problem is 157[u.t.] and the schedule length that PDF/IHS obtained within 10 minutes is 165[u.t.].
